io.branch.referral

Class ServerResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.branch.referral.ServerResponse

  • public class ServerResponse
extends java.lang.Object
    Class providing the structure of a HTTP response as recieved from the Branch API. Supports the following methods:
    • getTag()
    • getStatusCode()
    • setPost(Object)
    • getObject()
    • getArray()
    • getLinkData()

    • Constructor Detail

      • ServerResponse

        public ServerResponse(java.lang.String tag,
                      int statusCode)

        Constructor method for the ServerResponse class that allows for the instantiation of a server response object as a direct result of a server call. Omits BranchLinkData , so is used where that value is null or unavailable.

        Parameters:
        tag - A String value of the Tag attribute of the current link.
        statusCode - Integer value of the HTTP status code.

      • ServerResponse

        public ServerResponse(java.lang.String tag,
                      int statusCode,
                      BranchLinkData linkData)

        Main constructor method for the ServerResponse class that allows for the instantiation of a server response object as a direct result of a server call.

        Parameters:
        tag - A String value of the Tag attribute of the current link.
        statusCode - Integer value of the HTTP status code.
        linkData - A BranckLinkData object containing data attributes associated with a Branch link.

        public void setPost(java.lang.Object post)

        Sets the post data attached to the current server request, as a generic Object instance. This object can be type-cast by other methods within this class:

        Parameters:
        post - Generic Object instance containing post data associated with current response.
        See Also:

      • getObject

        public JSONObject getObject()

        Checks whether the post data associated with the current request is an instance of a JSONObject object, and if so type-casts it to the corresponding class type.

        Returns:
        A JSONObject containing the post data sent with a server request, or a null value if the post data is not of the JSONObject type.

      • getArray

        public JSONArray getArray()

        Checks whether the post data associated with the current request is an instance of a JSONArray object, and if so type-casts it to the corresponding class type.

        Returns:
        A JSONArray containing the post data sent with a server request, or a null value if the post data is not of the JSONArray type.

      • getLinkData

        public BranchLinkData getLinkData()

        Gets a BranchLinkData object containing the data associated with the current Branch link.

        A BranckLinkData object containing data attributes associated with a Branch link.
